rComments: Really good prof. She is a nice person and she teaches very well. You can EASILY pass the course without doing ANY of the readings. Just attend the lectures and write the essays. That's all you need as she is very articulate and explains everything very well.
She is helpful and nice, and brings me ice cream
Nice lady. However, her problem is that she "talks" at the class, rather than provoking critical discussion. This made her class long, boring and draining.

I think that she is a great prof.  However, she doesn't really put anything on the board so you have to listen and write very fast.  Also, there is a lot of reading.  Unless you a good essay writer, otherwise don't take this course since her assignments and finals are all essays.  Good Luck.
Good course, interesting assignments, though there were a little too much of it...too much reading too
fantastic teacher.  if you are getting tired of anthropology, just take a class with her and she will change your mind.
really good teacher, always willing to help, but too much essays
